title: Memory
author: abigail kelly
text: when i walked in those big school doors,  it reminded me i was in a new grade.  there were both big and small people wandering around trying to find thier classrooms,  all i remember was trying,  to find my door.  when i walked in it was scary,  but my parents were with me.  i sat down at my desk,  to start my work.  my parents took pictures of me and left,  saying goodbye and waving, giving me kisses and hugs, they said they'll miss me too.  when the bell rang i was excited,  the first day of 3rd grade was about to start.  my classmates were all nice.  i hung my bookbag on the hooks,  got my folders and papers out.  i was already excited for the last day of school,  the festiveties,  the fun,  the excitement.  field day & popsicles,  bounce houses,  a picnic lunch,  clap out,  awards ceremony,  getting our stars for good behavior,  wow!!!!!!!!!!! so many things to do on the last day of school.  i'll miss you and you'll miss me,  including my classmates who let me borrow thier things, my social studies teacher will miss me too,  leaving lander with a memory forever!

''goodbye,  goodbye,  goodbye!'' at first he just stared and stared,  then the eagle began to cry. . . ''aren't you a boy?'' i said my mind was in a whirl.   ''my wife will be here soon. '' he said.
